cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.HC, cs.SY, cs.LG. 

The paper describes an architecture for a robot that reasons about intentions and collaborates with humans. This involves reasoning with transition diagrams, non-monotonic logical reasoning, and probabilistic models of uncertainty. These topics are all closely related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and robotics (cs.RO). Additionally, the paper evaluates the architecture in the context of human-robot collaboration (cs.HC) and includes experiments on physical robots (cs.SY). Finally, the use of probabilistic models suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG).
